# Max n8n Agent Project Rules

## Project Structure
- Keep code modular and well-organized
- Use ES modules (type: "module" in package.json)
- Follow Node.js best practices

## Code Style
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add comments for complex logic
- Keep functions focused and single-purpose

## n8n Integration
- Follow n8n API patterns and conventions
- Handle errors gracefully
- Provide clear logging for debugging

## Cursor Cloud Agent — Job fit (full automation)

- **Auto-invoke Job-Advisor-for-Job-Seekers:** When the user asks for **job fit**, **resume–job match**, **company research for a role they are applying to**, **interview prep tied to a company/role**, **“run job fit”**, or similar end-to-end application analysis, **immediately** run `Task` with `subagent_type: "Job-Advisor-for-Job-Seekers"` and pass all supplied company, role, job URL, resume path, and LinkedIn URL. Do **not** require the user to type the agent name.
- **Auto-land on `main`:** After the Job Advisor workflow writes under `job-advisor-web/` and completes Step 5 (commit + push current branch), **automatically** run **Step 6** from `.cursor/agents/Job-Advisor-for-Job-Seekers.md`: merge the feature branch into **`main`** and **`git push origin main`** when branch protection allows; otherwise open a **non-draft** PR to `main` and **enable auto-merge** when permitted. Goal: GitHub / GitHub Pages and collaborators see updates on **`main`** without a separate user prompt.
- **Clean per-run dashboard URL in chat:** When presenting Job Advisor results (including after delegating to `Job-Advisor-for-Job-Seekers`), the reply **must** include **one line that is only** the full GitHub Pages URL `https://<owner>.github.io/<repo>/job-advisor-web/runs/<slug>/dashboard.html` (derive `owner`/`repo` from `git remote get-url origin`). Use **one** `job-advisor-web` segment in the path (not `job-advisor-web/job-advisor-web/`). **No** markdown links, backticks, bold, angle brackets, or extra characters on that line. See `.cursor/agents/Job-Advisor-for-Job-Seekers.md` (**Per-dashboard URL — user-facing output**).
